A vintage 1990s computer workstation viewed from above, showing a chunky beige CRT monitor displaying a grid of colorful application icons arranged in neat rows, each icon representing different business functions like calendars, filing cabinets, telephones, and clipboards. The desk is cluttered with period-appropriate items: a thick spiral-bound software manual, floppy disks scattered about, a coffee-stained mousepad, and a dusty keyboard with yellowed keys. Warm tungsten lighting casts nostalgic shadows across the scene. The color palette features muted teals, mustard yellows, and burgundy typical of early 90s software interfaces. Film grain texture and slightly faded colors evoke the feeling of rediscovering forgotten technology treasures in an old storage room.
